<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B00B32D927A3284F849F162F82C" author="Krober" box="[713,892,1958,1983]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527" refString="Krober, O. (1915 b) Die palaearktischen Arten der Gattung Conops L. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, Abteilung A, 81, 35 - 60." type="journal article" year="1915" yearSuffix="b">Kröber (1915b)</bibRefCitation>
separated 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32D927A33B0F849F744F82D" box="[1021,1370,1958,1983]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureotomentosa">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32D927A33B0F849F744F82D" box="[1021,1370,1958,1983]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">Physocephala aureotomentosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32D927A30DAF825F3CFF870" box="[151,465,1994,2019]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysorrhoea">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32D927A30DAF825F3CFF870" box="[151,465,1994,2019]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">Physocephala chrysorrhoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by means of the wing colouration: the dark colouration in cell r2+3 does not reach to the tip of the cell in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B3102FF76F001FF23" box="[335,543,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureotomentosa">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B3102FF76F001FF23" box="[335,543,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. aureotomentosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This character turns out to be very variable in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B347EFF76F6FAFF23" box="[1075,1252,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysorrhoea">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B347EFF76F6FAFF23" box="[1075,1252,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. chrysorrhoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B35CAFF76F355FF47" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureotomentosa">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B35CAFF76F355FF47" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. aureotomentosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
falls within the variation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B32C4FF52F124FF46" box="[649,826,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysorrhoea">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B32C4FF52F124FF46" box="[649,826,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. chrysorrhoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is accordingly placed as a junior synonym.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836F1B32C927B30DAFEEAF035FE8F" blockId="7.[151,1437,260,896]" box="[151,555,260,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B30DAFEEAF2B4FE8F" box="[151,170,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">=</emphasis>
