</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836F1B32C927B30DAFEC8F0CBFEF7" blockId="7.[151,1437,260,896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="AB7711DFB32C927B30DAFEC8F0CBFEF7" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B30DAFEC8F06AFED3" authority="Zimina 1974: 132" authorityName="Zimina" authorityPageNumber="132" authorityYear="1974" box="[151,628,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emiliae">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B30DAFEC8F38CFED3" box="[151,402,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">Physocephala emiliae</emphasis>
<treatmentCitation id="0AC610E0B32C927B31D3FEC8F06AFED3" author="Zimina" box="[414,628,295,320]" page="132" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" year="1974">
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B00B32C927B31D3FEC8F029FED3" author="Zimina" box="[414,567,295,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" refString="Zimina, L. V. (1974) A new species of Physocephala (Diptera, Conopidae), a parasite of bees of the genus Nomia in Pamir. Zoologiceskij Zurnal, 52, 1732 - 1733. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1974">Zimina 1974</bibRefCitation>
: 132
</treatmentCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; type-locality: “Pamir, Lyangar on Pyandzhe, 
<quantity id="4C9F9B14B32C927B34D5FEC7F6F6FED3" box="[1176,1256,296,320]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" unit="m" value="2800.0">2800m</quantity>
” [translated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B00B32C927B30DAFEA3F3DEFEF7" author="Clements" box="[151,448,332,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" refString="Clements, D. K. &amp; Vincent, H. (2001) The conopid taxa described by L. V. Zimina from the former Soviet Union (Diptera, Conopidae). Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 137, 33 - 48." type="journal article" year="2001">Clements &amp; Vincent 2001</bibRefCitation>
]; holotypus ♀ [ZMUM].
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836F1B32C927B308AFE9FF669FD8B" blockId="7.[151,1437,260,896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">
I was able to examine 
<typeStatus id="54DC8853B32C927B31A5FE9FF04DFE1B" box="[488,595,368,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B32C5FE80F199FE1B" box="[648,903,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emiliae">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B32C5FE80F199FE1B" box="[648,903,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">Physocephala emiliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and these specimens accord with European specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B317FFE7BF072FE3E" box="[306,620,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysorrhoea">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B317FFE7BF072FE3E" box="[306,620,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">Physocephala chrysorrhoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The characters set out in the original description fit with the concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B30DAFE56F351FE43" box="[151,335,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysorrhoea">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B30DAFE56F351FE43" box="[151,335,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. chrysorrhoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as described above, and therefore 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B32B4FE56F173FE43" box="[761,877,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emiliae">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B32B4FE56F173FE43" box="[761,877,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. emiliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is herewith placed as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B35CAFE56F333FE66" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysorrhoea">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B35CAFE56F333FE66" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. chrysorrhoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B00B32C927B310FFE33F3F4FE67" author="Zimina" box="[322,490,476,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" refString="Zimina, L. V. (1974) A new species of Physocephala (Diptera, Conopidae), a parasite of bees of the genus Nomia in Pamir. Zoologiceskij Zurnal, 52, 1732 - 1733. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1974">Zimina (1974)</bibRefCitation>
used only characters of colouration and size to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B348FFE32F729FE66" box="[1218,1335,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emiliae">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B348FFE32F729FE66" box="[1218,1335,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. emiliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B35CAFE32F333FD8B" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysorrhoea">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B35CAFE32F333FD8B" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. chrysorrhoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and these characters fall within the range of variation of the latter species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836F1B32C927B30DAFDCAF033FDAF" blockId="7.[151,1437,260,896]" box="[151,557,548,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B30DAFDCAF2B4FDAF" box="[151,170,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">=</emphasis>
