<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B30FCFDCAF33EFDAF" box="[177,288,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. zaitzevi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B00B32C927B316AFDCBF3A0FDAF" author="Zimina" box="[295,446,548,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" refString="Zimina, L. V. (1979) A new conopid species (Diptera, Conopidae) from Turkmenstan Trudy Vsesojuznogo Entomologicheskogo Obshchestva, 61, 196 - 197. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1979">Zimina, 1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B3188FDCBF033FDAF" bold="true" box="[453,557,548,572]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2205798B32C927B3188FDCBF033FDAF" box="[453,557,548,572]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836F1B32C927B30DAFDA8F1E3FD17" blockId="7.[151,1437,260,896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="AB7711DFB32C927B30DAFDA8F1E3FD17" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B30DAFDA8F077FDF3" authority="Zimina 1979: 196" authorityName="Zimina" authorityPageNumber="196" authorityYear="1979" box="[151,617,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaitzevi">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B30DAFDA8F38FFDF3" box="[151,401,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">Physocephala zaitzevi</emphasis>
<treatmentCitation id="0AC610E0B32C927B31D6FDA8F077FDF3" author="Zimina" box="[411,617,583,608]" page="196" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" year="1979">
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B00B32C927B31D6FDA8F02FFDF3" author="Zimina" box="[411,561,583,608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" refString="Zimina, L. V. (1979) A new conopid species (Diptera, Conopidae) from Turkmenstan Trudy Vsesojuznogo Entomologicheskogo Obshchestva, 61, 196 - 197. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1979">Zimina 1979</bibRefCitation>
: 196
</treatmentCitation>
</taxonomicName>
–197; type-locality: “Ipaj-Kala, 
<quantity id="4C9F9B14B32C927B3395FDA8F609FDF3" box="[984,1047,583,608]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" unit="km" value="30.0">30km</quantity>
to the S.W. of Bakharden, 
<quantity id="4C9F9B14B32C927B3518FDA7F786FDF3" box="[1365,1432,584,608]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" unit="m" value="100.0">100m</quantity>
, Turkmeniya”, translated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B00B32C927B319DFD83F0E9FD17" author="Clements" box="[464,759,620,645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" refString="Clements, D. K. &amp; Vincent, H. (2001) The conopid taxa described by L. V. Zimina from the former Soviet Union (Diptera, Conopidae). Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 137, 33 - 48." type="journal article" year="2001">Clements &amp; Vincent 2001</bibRefCitation>
; holotypus ♀ [ZMUM]
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836F1B32C927B308AFD7FF0B0FCEC" blockId="7.[151,1437,260,896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">
I was able to examine the 
<typeStatus id="54DC8853B32C927B324DFD60F07CFD3B" box="[512,610,655,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B32C3FD60F18FFD3B" box="[654,913,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B32C3FD60F193FD3B" box="[654,909,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaitzevi">Physocephala zaitzevi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
After seeing more material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B34B2FD60F333FD5E" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysorrhoea">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B34B2FD60F333FD5E" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">Physocephala chrysorrhoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and realising that several previously undetermined Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B3449FD5BF6BFFD5E" box="[1028,1185,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B3449FD5BF6BFFD5E" box="[1028,1185,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">Physocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in fact belong to that species, I have come to the conclusion that 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B3231FD36F13AFD63" box="[636,804,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysorhoea">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B3231FD36F13AFD63" box="[636,804,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. chrysorhoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an extremely variable species and that 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B34B8FD36F77BFD63" box="[1269,1381,729,752]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaitzevi">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B34B8FD36F77BFD63" box="[1269,1381,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. zaitzevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
falls within its variation range. The characters set out in the original description also fit completely to this concept. Contrary to the description of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B00B32C927B31BEFCF0F089FCAB" author="Zimina" box="[499,663,799,824]" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" refString="Zimina, L. V. (1979) A new conopid species (Diptera, Conopidae) from Turkmenstan Trudy Vsesojuznogo Entomologicheskogo Obshchestva, 61, 196 - 197. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1979">Zimina (1979)</bibRefCitation>
I cannot find any differences in the shape or the size of the female theca between 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B310EFCAAF3A8FCCF" box="[323,438,837,860]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaitzevi">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B310EFCAAF3A8FCCF" box="[323,438,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. zaitzevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B31BFFCAAF0B9FCCE" box="[498,679,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysorrhoea">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B31BFFCAAF0B9FCCE" box="[498,679,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">P. chrysorrhoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, either. Therefore, I herewith propose 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B3424FCABF77AFCCF" box="[1129,1380,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaitzevi">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B3424FCABF77AFCCF" box="[1129,1380,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">Physocephala zaitzevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D72B32C927B3120FC88F0B8FC13" box="[365,678,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysorrhoea">
<emphasis id="B913EAE3B32C927B3120FC88F0B8FC13" box="[365,678,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="528">Physocephala chrysorrhoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
